<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by BigDrew:
[B]So, my wife's been playing EQ for a while, and I'm going to start playing soon. She spends a good deal of time fishing, and maxing out her fishing skill, so I have a question:

Why do people fish? From what I can see, you get one of 4 items: fresh fish, fish scales, sandals, and daggers. I can see that some of these might be useful for a low-level character, but once you are beyond lvl 4 or 5, it seems like hunting monsters would be a more effective use of your time. If you are a spell user and you want fish scales to swim underwater for extended periods, you can always buy some. So why do so many people fish in EQ? Actually, you could probably ask that question in the real world as well ;-P

I'm sure there's some benefit I just haven't thought of, so please enlighten me!

Thanks,

    Drew[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
